From: Sagi Grimberg <sagi@grimberg.me>
Date: Wed, 29 Mar 2017 20:54:15 +0300
Subject: nvme-loop: increment request retries counter before requeuing
References: bsc#1037838
Git-commit: 7d9a5e7176c60673b283bdb0e507d288b48d9528
Patch-Mainline: v4.7

This way our max retry limit holds as well.

Signed-off-by: Sagi Grimberg <sagi@grimberg.me>
Reviewed-by: Max Gurtovoy <maxg@mellanox.com>
Reviewed-by: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
Signed-off-by: Jens Axboe <axboe@fb.com>
Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/nvme/target/loop.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/nvme/target/loop.c b/drivers/nvme/target/loop.c
index e9c4ad0..6e8962c 100644
--- a/drivers/nvme/target/loop.c
+++ b/drivers/nvme/target/loop.c
@@ -98,6 +98,7 @@ static void nvme_loop_complete_rq(struct request *req)
 
 	if (unlikely(req->errors)) {
 		if (nvme_req_needs_retry(req, req->errors)) {
+			req->retries++;
 			nvme_requeue_req(req);
 			return;
 		}
